definition.value: A member of the class of furoic acids that is 2-furoic acid substituted at position 5 by a dihydroxymethyl group.
An alkane that is decane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 3, 5 and 8. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
A long-chain alkane that is heptadecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6, 10 and 14. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
A long-chain alkane that is heptadecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6, 10 and 15. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
A hydroxypolyether that is the monomethyl ether derivative of triethylene glycol. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
A primary alcohol that is 1-octanol substituted by a butyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
An alkane that is  octane substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 5. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
A fatty alcohol that is 1-dodecanol substituted by methyl groups at positions 3, 7 and 11. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
A fatty alcohol that is 3-octanol substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 7. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
An alkane that is undecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 8. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
An alkane that is  dodecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 4 and 6. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
An alkane that is undecane substituted by a methyl group at position 4. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
A 1-acyl-2-tetradecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-acyl group is specified as tetradecanoyl (myristoyl).
An unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of trans-2-dodecenoic acid obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A long-chain alkane that is tridecane substituted by a methyl group at position 2. Metabolite observed in cancer metabolism.
An alkane that is dodecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 7 and 10.
An  alkane that is  undecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 4 and 6.
A long-chain alkane consisting of an unbranched chain of 44 carbon atoms.
An L-tyrosine derivative that is L-DOPA in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the phenyl ring is replaced by a cysteinyl group. Found in the urine of patients with melanoma.
An L-tyrosine derivative that is L-DOPA in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 on the phenyl ring are replaced by cysteinyl groups. Found in the urine of patients with melanoma.
A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of dodecanoic (lauric) acid.
A straight-chain saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of pentacosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A linear dextrin or short chained amylose (DP 20-30) that can be produced by enzymatic hydrolysis of the alpha-1,6 glycosidic bonds or debranching amylopectin.

Any of the lignans with a 9-aryl-1-oxo-1,3-dihydronaphtho[2,3-c]furan-4-yl glycoside skeleton originally isolated from Cleistanthus collinus, a toxic deciduous shrub. While all parts of the plant are poisonous, the leaves in particular are used as a suicide poison by young women in rural parts of southern India. Cleistanthins A and B have been particularly associated with the toxicity of the plant, with cleistanthin A being more potent than cleistanthin B.
A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of tetradecanoic (myristic) acid.
A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted with a methoxy group at C-3 and a polyprenyl chain of unspecified length at C-5.
The hydroxybenzoate anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid. The major species present at pH 7.3.
A dihydroxybenzoic acid where the hydroxy groups are at the 4- and 5-positions together with a heptaprenyl group at the 3-position.
A 3,4-dihydroxy-5-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 7 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A dihydroxybenzoic acid where the hydroxy groups are at the 4- and 5-positions together with a octaprenyl group at the 3-position.
A 3,4-dihydroxy-5-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 8 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid in which the polyprenyl component is specified as octaprenyl.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl component is specified as octaprenyl.
A lysophosphatidylcholine with defined stereochemistry where the position of the acyl group is unknown.
A phosphatidylcholine 37:4 in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A N-hexacosenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine consisting of sphingosine as the sphingoid base acylated at the N atom by a (17Z)-hexacosenoyl group.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the acyl group specified is heneicosanoyl.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in whihc the acyl group specified is nonadecanoyl.
A N-octadecenolsphingosine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is 9Z-octadecenoyl.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the acyl group specified is heptadecanoyl.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted at position 3 by a heptaprenyl group.
A N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is tetracosanoyl.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted at position 3 by a nonaprenyl group.
A N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is heptadecanoyl.
A  1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) respectively.
A 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl  and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.
